title: Johari: No necessity yet to provide aid for poor in regard to fuel prices
text:
More 
While the government is considering ways to provide aid for the poor should fuel prices go up, this is currently unnecessary. This is because the current prices of between US$45 and US$55 a barrel are still reasonable, said Finance Minister II Johari Abdul Ghani, but it would be a different story if the prices are much higher.
